A '''bend stiffener''' is a type of [[cable protection system]]. They are conically shaped polyurethane mouldings designed to add local stiffness to a riser, flowline, cable or [[Umbilical cable|umbilical]]. They limit the bending stresses and curvature to acceptable levels.<ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.abcosubsea.com/umbilical-management2/bend-stiffener.html |title = Bend Stiffeners |website = wwww.abcosubsea.com |accessdate = May 9, 2013 }}</ref> They are used in the [[oil and gas industry]] as part of [[Offshore drilling|offshore deep sea drilling]] operations.
==Companies that Manufacture Bend Stiffeners== * [http://www.abcosubsea.com/ ABCO Subsea] * [http://www.uw-elast.com/ UW-Elast Sweden] * [http://www.exsto.com/ EXSTO] * [http://www.balltec.com/ Balltec Ltd] * [http://www.firstsubsea.com/ First Subsea] * [http://www.risertec.com RiserTec] * [http://www.trelleborg.com/en/offshore/ Trelleborg Offshore] * [http://fesinternational.com/ FES International] * [http://www.groupe-courbis.com/off-shore-oil-gas.html COURBIS Group] * [http://www.bardotgroup.com Bardot Group]
