An '''inertial platform''', also known as a '''gyroscopic platform''' or '''stabilized platform''', is a system using [[gyroscope]]s to maintain a platform in a fixed orientation in space despite the movement of the vehicle that it is attached to. These can then be used to stabilize [[gunsight]]s in [[tank]]s, [[anti-aircraft artillery]] on ships, and as the basis for older mechanically-based [[inertial navigation system]]s.

